56w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"/></picture></a></figure><p>h/t Jack Farley </p><p>The panic began when SVB tried to raise capital to cover its losses. As Lulu Cheng explains this went terribly wrong. </p><a href="https://twitter.com/lulumeservey/status/1634232327168557057?s=20" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/qm7dFARssbA4MHKgqPu06aUB9GBAZ5jhOQFWgbHTsds=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvdHdpdHRlcl9uYW1lL3dfOTYvbHVsdW1lc2VydmV5LmpwZw==" alt="Twitter avatar for @lulumeservey" loading="lazy"/>Lulu Cheng Meservey @lulumeserveySVB made the responsible decision to strengthen its financial position with a cap raise.

